OL,3,CWhat key decisions is the government
OL,4,Cfacing over welfare?
OL,6,FSome of the reported changes to the
OL,7,Fthresholds suggest people who need
OL,8,Fhelping cooking a meal will get
OL,9,Feligibility points, but those who can
OL,10,Fuse a microwave won't.
OL,12,FSimilarly, people who need help
OL,13,Fwashing their upper body will be
OL,14,Fincluded, but not those who need
OL,15,Fsupport washing their hair and lower
OL,16,Fbody. And those who need help going to
OL,17,Fthe toilet will get points, but people
OL,18,Fwho need reminding to go won't.
